cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS

The paper describes a classical planning system based on heuristic search, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically deals with planning problems encoded in the propositional fragment of PDDL2.2, which is a subfield of automated planning and scheduling (cs.PL). The paper also discusses search algorithms and data structures, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents novel techniques for search control, which involve optimization and efficiency, making it relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
